Two loves I have, of comfort and despair,
That like two spirits do suggest me still.
My better angel is a man right fair,
With his short gray hair behind his ears,
And yet in his way shows,
His sweet, gentle touch, his gentle heart,
That all love, all hate, all lust,
Are all what they are, all that I love.
  Then my love is the better,
  That more of him is my best.
    Then my love is the better;
    Then my love is the worse;
    Then my love is my best;
    Then my love is my worst.
    Then my love is my worst.
 


